ing in motorcycle damage, serious injury or death.","The front forks comprise of many precision machined parts.","Total cleanliness must be observed at all times and assembly must take place in a dirt/dust-free environment. ","Dirt ingress may cause damage to the fork parts, leading to incorrect operation, instability, loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","Springs under load can cause injury if released suddenly.","Always wear suitable protective eye wear and release the spring slowly.","Failure to wear protective eye wear may cause injury to the eyes.","Perform the following operations:","Front Fork - Removal","Using a soft jawed vice, clamp the ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool"," so the fork can be mounted vertically.","With the outer fork top cap facing upwards, gently clamp the outer fork tube into ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Using ","Service Tool 37174038"," carefully unscrew the top cap from the outer fork tube.","Top cap ","Outer fork tube","Remove the fork assembly from the ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Pour out the fork oil into a suitable container.","Position the fork assembly vertically allowing access to the lock nut.","Gently clamp the inner fork tube into ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Top cap ","Lock nut","Damper rod","Outer fork tube ","Using ","Service Tool 37174038"," on the top cap, release the lock nut as shown in the image below","Remove the top cap.","Remove the lock nut from the damper rod.","Outer fork tube ","Damper rod","Lock nut","Top cap ","Service Tool 37174038","Remove the fork from the ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Mount the fork horizontally, clamping the outer fork tube.","Using a soft jawed vice, clamp the ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool"," so the fork can be mounted horizontally.","Remove the dust shield from the fork outer tube.","Inner fork tube ","Dust shield","Outer fork tube","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool","Release the dust seal from the outer fork tube.","Outer fork tube ","Dust seal",